<Issue id="21023" key="FABG-50" number="50" project="10610" reporter="troyronda" assignee="sandrav" creator="troyronda" type="10001" summary="Channel Client" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2017-09-27 15:00:45.0" updated="2018-07-20 19:17:02.0" resolutiondate="2017-10-04 17:35:18.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="32849"> <description><! CDATA A channel client instance provides a handler to interact with peers on specified channel.  An application that requires interaction with multiple channels should create a separate  instance of the channel client for each channel.     Channel client supports non-admin functions: query, execute transaction and receive chain code events.  Sample usage:     sdk, err := fabapi.NewSDK(fabapi.Options\{ConfigFile: "myconfig.yaml"})  chClient, err := sdk.NewChannelClient("mychannel", "User1")  _, err = chClient.ExecuteTx(apitxn.ExecuteTxRequest\{ChaincodeID: "example_cc", Fcn: "invoke", Args: moveFundsArgs})  result, err := chClient.Query(apitxn.QueryRequest\{ChaincodeID: "example_cc", Fcn: "invoke",  Args: queryArgs})  chClient.Close()  ></description> </Issue>
